    "_postman_id": "b5bb985f-f087-4fd2-bb72-23be51461bb9",
    "name": "Users API Testing",
    "description": "## API Testing Project – Users endpoint\n\nDescription:\n\nThis project contains API tests executed using Postman for the public endpoint:\n\n[https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users](https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/users)\n\nThe objective of this project is to validate API behavior using functional and negative testing techniques.\n\n## Test scope\n\nThe following validations were performed:\n\n• Status code validation\n\n• Response time validation\n\n• JSON structure validation\n\n• Data type validation\n\n• Negative testing\n\n• Invalid input testing\n\n• Non existing resources testing\n\n## Test cases included\n\nTC01 – Get all users\n\nTC02 – Get user by valid ID\n\nTC03 – Get non existing user\n\nTC04 – Invalid ID format\n\nTC05 – Boundary value (ID = 0)\n\nTC06 – Negative ID\n\nTC07 – Decimal ID\n\nTC08 – Empty ID\n\n## Tools used\n\nPostman\n\nJSONPlaceholder API\n\n## Test approach\n\nTests were executed manually and automated using Postman test scripts.\n\nEach request includes automated validations for:\n\n• Status codes\n\n• Response structure\n\n• Required fields\n\n• Data types\n\n## Observations\n\nThe API returns the same response for:\n\n• Invalid ID format\n\n• Non existing ID\n\nThis could make error differentiation harder in real scenarios.\n\n## Author\n\nQA Practice Project created as part of API Testing learning path.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "52379920",
    "_collection_link": "https://go.postman.co/collection/52379920-b5bb985f-f087-4fd2-bb72-23be51461bb9?source=collection_link"
  },
